      • FAKE_LAST_UPDATE_TIME_DATE

        public static final java.util.Date FAKE_LAST_UPDATE_TIME_DATE
        This effective time has to be manually set on the TerminologymetadataPackage.getCodeSystemVersion_LastUpdateDate() feature before re-versioning an already existing version.

        This is the workaround to lie to CDO about a change, since the commit timestamp not known at commit time but on change processing time.

      • VERSION_EFFECTIVE_DATE_COMPARATOR
